<p>I need to upload a programmatically created image from iOS into a WebGL texture. The image is created fine, but in WebGL it renders as a black box. </p>  <p>I am able to get other images from the bundle into webGL as long as they're created in texturepacker and using texturepacker's premultiplied alpha option. Regular pngs in the bundle also look like black boxes. </p>  <p>Looking into it more, it appears that the <code>CGImageRef</code> that I create has an alpha info of <code>kCGImageAlphaPremultipliedFirst</code>. After I save it to the bundle as a png pulling it back out shows an alpha mode of <code>kCGImageAlphaLast</code>- leading me to believe that the alpha has become unpremultiplied and causing this issue. </p>  <p>So I'm wondering: is there a way to save a png into the bundle with premultiplied alpha? Is this even the right track or should I be working on getting WebGL to deal with non-premultipliedalpha images? </p>  <p>Here's my texture uploading code for reference: </p>  <pre><code>    gl.pixelStorei(gl.UNPACK_PREMULTIPLY_ALPHA_WEBGL, 0);     var texture = gl.createTexture();     gl.activeTexture(gl.TEXTURE0);     gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texture);     gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, gl.LINEAR);     gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, gl.LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST);     gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_S, gl.CLAMP_TO_EDGE);     gl.texParameteri(gl.TEXTURE_2D, gl.TEXTURE_WRAP_T, gl.CLAMP_TO_EDGE);     gl.texImage2D(gl.TEXTURE_2D, 0, gl.RGBA, gl.RGBA, gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE, image);     gl.generateMipmap(gl.TEXTURE_2D);     gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, null);     return texture; </code></pre>